==English==
===Adjective===
'''gelid'''
#Very cold
#Icy or frosty

Examples:

"a man of gelid reserve" -- New Yorker

"In the worst of summer the tower remained cool, yet the air seemed feverish and gelid when sisters of different Ajahs came to close." ''Knife of Dreams'' Robert Jordan

===Etymology===
From the Latin [[gelidus]].

